<paragraph id="1E3A36DCAB77FFFBFF20614C9B58588C" blockId="42.[742,1271,1326,1731]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
DIAGNOSIS: This subgenus is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D9854D5FAB77FFFBFF28612E9BF85B67" authorityName="Engel, Brooks, and Yanega" authorityYear="1997" box="[779,958,1356,1379]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megommation" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Cleptommation">
<emphasis id="2CF1EACEAB77FFFBFF28612E9BF85B67" box="[779,958,1356,1379]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Cleptommation</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, particularly in the male sex where both share the presence of dense plumose setae surrounding the propodeal spiracle. 
<taxonomicName id="D9854D5FAB77FFFBFF1261C69BA25BBF" authorityName="Engel, Brooks, and Yanega" authorityYear="1997" box="[817,996,1444,1467]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megommation" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Cleptommation">
<emphasis id="2CF1EACEAB77FFFBFF1261C69BA25BBF" box="[817,996,1444,1467]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Cleptommation</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, lacks a scopa, has a bladelike mandible, lacks a basitibial plate, and differs in the structure of the male metasomal sterna. 
<taxonomicName id="D9854D5FAB77FFFBF82F619E9CE75817" box="[1036,1185,1532,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megommation" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Megaloptina">
<emphasis id="2CF1EACEAB77FFFBF82F619E9CE75817" box="[1036,1185,1532,1555]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Megaloptina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="D9854D5FAB77FFFBFF08627B9BFD5834" authorityName="Engel, Brooks, and Yanega" authorityYear="1997" box="[811,955,1561,1584]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megommation" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Stilbochlora">
<emphasis id="2CF1EACEAB77FFFBFF08627B9BFD5834" box="[811,955,1561,1584]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Stilbochlora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the presence of a propodeal tuft of setae in males and the short basitibial plate with weakly developed borders.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="569F6557AB77FFFAFF2062EC98A75D1C" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph id="1E3A36DCAB77FFFAFF2062EC99105C81" blockId="42.[742,1271,1326,1731]" lastBlockId="43.[161,690,182,851]" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
DESCRIPTION: As for the genus with the following additions: 
<emphasis id="2CF1EACEAB77FFFBFFFD62C99C0658C7" bold="true" box="[990,1088,1707,1731]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Female.</emphasis>
Mandible with moderate subapical tooth. Labral basal elevation orbicular; teeth weak. Clypeal apex concave (fig. 12). Hypostomal ridge carinate. Ocelli not greatly enlarged. Pronotal dorsal ridge rounded. Scopa present. Basitibial plate extremely short, borders faint. Inner hind tibial spur pectinate. 
<emphasis id="2CF1EACEAB76FFFAFD55650499FA5F7A" bold="true" box="[374,444,358,382]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Male.</emphasis>
Labrum without distal process. Antenna extending back to scutellum; F1 longer than F2. Dense patch of plumose setae at propodeal spiracle. Metasoma oval. Apical margin of S2 unmodified. Apical margin of S3 with median projection. Apical margin of S4 unmodified. Apical margin of S5 emarginate. Apical margin of S7 with median projection. Apical margin of S8 unmodified.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E3A36DCAB76FFFAFC9D66EE98A75D1C" blockId="43.[161,690,182,851]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
REVISIONS: There are presently only two described species, 
<taxonomicName id="D9854D5FAB76FFFAFDA266CB997F5CD9" authority="(Dalla Torre)" baseAuthorityName="Dalla Torre" baseAuthorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megommation" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="festivagum">
<emphasis id="2CF1EACEAB76FFFAFDA266CB9AF75CC4" box="[385,689,681,704]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Megommation festivagum</emphasis>
(Dalla Torre)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D9854D5FAB76FFFAFD5266A59A3A5CD9" authority="(Cockerell)" baseAuthorityName="Cockerell" box="[369,636,710,734]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ogilviei">
<emphasis id="2CF1EACEAB76FFFAFD5266A599CF5CDA" box="[369,393,711,734]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2CF1EACEAB76FFFAFDB466A599A85CDA" box="[407,494,711,734]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">ogilviei</emphasis>
(Cockerell)
</taxonomicName>
, and at least one undescribed species (personal obs.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="569F6557AB76FFFAFC9D677C99B95D57" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="distribution">
